1
00:00:01,085 --> 00:00:02,545
[ mouse squeaks ]

2
00:00:02,628 --> 00:00:04,130
[ penguins wenk ]

3
00:00:06,215 --> 00:00:07,299
[ all cheering ]

4
00:00:10,386 --> 00:00:11,512
[ screeches ]

5
00:00:13,347 --> 00:00:14,348
D> Adventure Time )

6
00:00:14,432 --> 00:00:16,434
» Come on, grab your friends »

7
00:00:16,517 --> 00:00:18,477
» We'll go to very distant lands J

8
00:00:18,561 --> 00:00:20,604
» With Jake the Dog
and Finn the Human »

9
00:00:20,688 --> 00:00:22,273
D The fun will never end >

10
00:00:22,356 --> 00:00:24,442
D It's Adventure Time »

11
00:00:32,658 --> 00:00:36,537
[ squeaking ]

12
00:00:38,330 --> 00:00:40,082
Aw, yes!

13
00:00:40,166 --> 00:00:41,625
The storm has passed!

14
00:00:41,709 --> 00:00:42,877
Jake!

15
00:00:44,753 --> 00:00:46,505
Hoo! Hoo.

16
00:00:46,589 --> 00:00:48,215
Jake.

17
00:00:48,299 --> 00:00:49,842
Nachos.

18
00:00:49,925 --> 00:00:53,053
Nachos.
| love nachos.

19
00:00:55,181 --> 00:00:58,184
| love nachos even more while
looking out the window.

20
00:01:04,732 --> 00:01:09,570
[ wind howling ]

21
00:01:09,653 --> 00:01:12,656
Hmm. Does that box have
a face on it?

22
00:01:12,740 --> 00:01:14,450
A face...

23
00:01:14,533 --> 00:01:16,202
gotta make sure.

24
00:01:19,205 --> 00:01:20,915
[ gasps ]

25
00:01:20,998 --> 00:01:23,167
There's a box outside
with a face on it!

26
00:01:23,250 --> 00:01:24,543
It might be a box man.

27
00:01:24,627 --> 00:01:26,754
He's all soggy and dirty.
Want to check it out?

28
00:01:26,837 --> 00:01:28,672
NEVA

29
00:01:28,756 --> 00:01:31,008
'Chos!

30
00:01:31,091 --> 00:01:32,635
[ munching ]

31
00:01:32,718 --> 00:01:33,928
I'm gonna check it out.

32
00:01:34,011 --> 00:01:35,971
- Yeah, whatever.

33
00:01:39,433 --> 00:01:41,602
Hmm.
Where'd your face go?

34
00:01:45,189 --> 00:01:47,483
Whoa!

35
00:01:50,027 --> 00:01:51,779
Okay. Shh.

36
00:01:51,862 --> 00:01:53,864
Are you lost,
little cardboard dude?

37
00:01:55,991 --> 00:01:57,576
[ cat meows ]

38
00:01:57,660 --> 00:01:59,578
Jake! There seems to be
a lost cat

39
00:01:59,662 --> 00:02:01,413
bumping around in a box!

40
00:02:01,497 --> 00:02:04,124
JAKE: Yeah, that's great.
Get it out of here!

41
00:02:05,334 --> 00:02:06,794
Getting no help
from him, | guess.

42
00:02:06,877 --> 00:02:09,171
Do you know where
your home is?

43
00:02:09,255 --> 00:02:10,631
[ cat meows ]

44
00:02:10,714 --> 00:02:12,675
Okay. I'll follow you.

45
00:02:27,898 --> 00:02:29,483
Whoa.

46
00:02:29,567 --> 00:02:31,777
Is this your kingdom?
- [ cat meows ]

47
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:34,113
It's wonderful!

48
00:02:34,196 --> 00:02:36,156
[ cats meowing ]

49
00:02:43,414 --> 00:02:44,331
[ cat meows ]

50
00:02:44,415 --> 00:02:45,708
[ laughing ]

51
00:02:45,791 --> 00:02:51,380
[ trumpets blaring ]

52
00:02:51,463 --> 00:02:53,507
That must be your prince.

53
00:02:55,509 --> 00:02:57,511
Huh?

54
00:03:01,348 --> 00:03:02,433
Huh?

55
00:03:02,516 --> 00:03:05,978
A prince wouldn't steal
from his subjects.

56
00:03:09,231 --> 00:03:10,274
Aww!

57
00:03:10,357 --> 00:03:12,318
[ cat meows ]

58
00:03:15,404 --> 00:03:16,655
Switched?

59
00:03:16,739 --> 00:03:18,240
[ gasps ]
Of course!

60
00:03:18,324 --> 00:03:19,658
You must be the real prince,

61
00:03:19,742 --> 00:03:21,327
and
that thief took your place!

62
00:03:21,410 --> 00:03:24,246
Is that right, little prince?

63
00:03:24,330 --> 00:03:28,208
[ cat meows ]

64
00:03:28,292 --> 00:03:30,919
[ breathes deeply ]
Don't worry, your majesty.

65
00:03:31,003 --> 00:03:33,130
I'll help you reclaim
your kingdom.

66
00:03:33,213 --> 00:03:35,924
[ cat meows ]

67
00:03:36,008 --> 00:03:38,135
[ cat purring ]

68
00:03:38,218 --> 00:03:40,054
[ mid-tempo music plays, stops ]

69
00:03:40,137 --> 00:03:41,972
Why do you hate cats, Jake?

70
00:03:42,056 --> 00:03:44,183
Move your face.
You're messing up the game.

71
00:03:44,266 --> 00:03:46,226
Anyway, | don't want to talk
about it.

72
00:03:46,310 --> 00:03:50,522
It's personal.
Cats know what they did.

73
00:03:50,606 --> 00:03:53,275
Aah! Aah!

74
00:03:53,359 --> 00:03:54,401
Is Jake okay?

75
00:03:54,485 --> 00:03:56,278
[ groaning ]

76
00:03:56,362 --> 00:03:57,404
No!

77
00:03:57,488 --> 00:03:59,907
I'm pretty dang far from okay!

78
00:03:59,990 --> 00:04:01,575
There's a little shard
of tortilla chip

79
00:04:01,659 --> 00:04:03,202
caught between
my teeth.

80
00:04:03,285 --> 00:04:05,245
[ groans ]

81
00:04:10,918 --> 00:04:13,212
First, we have to expose
the traitor's deception.

82
00:04:13,295 --> 00:04:15,923
Hmm. Aha.

83
00:04:16,006 --> 00:04:17,925
That's a counterfeit crown,

84
00:04:18,008 --> 00:04:20,594
hewn from the liar's own
boxflesh.

85
00:04:20,678 --> 00:04:21,595
Hmm.

86
00:04:21,679 --> 00:04:24,431
It looks like your crown was
torn off by some -- ah!

87
00:04:24,515 --> 00:04:26,100
[ cat meows ]

88
00:04:26,183 --> 00:04:28,060
Your crown was lost, you say?

89
00:04:28,143 --> 00:04:30,145
[ cat meows ]

90
00:04:32,815 --> 00:04:33,857
During the storm?

91
00:04:33,941 --> 00:04:34,942
[ cat meows ]

92
00:04:35,025 --> 00:04:37,403
The same storm that sent you
hurtling through the woods?

93
00:04:37,486 --> 00:04:38,862
[ cat meows ]

94
00:04:38,946 --> 00:04:40,989
Until you were delivered
unto my doorstep?

95
00:04:41,073 --> 00:04:43,992
[ cat meows ]

96
00:04:44,076 --> 00:04:45,160
Right.

97
00:04:45,244 --> 00:04:47,996
So it's definitely
in the woods somewhere.

98
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:49,498
All we have to do is
find your crown

99
00:04:49,581 --> 00:04:52,960
to prove to the people
that you're the real prince.

100
00:04:56,547 --> 00:04:57,881
[ sniffs ]

101
00:04:57,965 --> 00:05:00,008
Mm. Um...

102
00:05:00,092 --> 00:05:03,095
I'm gonna wait over by the
gates, your highness.

103
00:05:10,853 --> 00:05:14,815
Mm-nah, mm-nah,
mm-nah.

104
00:05:14,898 --> 00:05:18,277
Get big and the chip will
fall out of your teeth.

105
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:20,988
Ha! You think | can
stretch out of everything?

106
00:05:21,071 --> 00:05:22,656
You're so naive.

107
00:05:22,740 --> 00:05:25,451
To live life,
you need problems.

108
00:05:25,534 --> 00:05:27,661
That's stupid!

109
00:05:27,745 --> 00:05:30,038
If you get everything you want
the minute you want it,

110
00:05:30,122 --> 00:05:32,082
what's the point of living?

111
00:05:36,128 --> 00:05:38,130
[ grunting ]

112
00:05:43,552 --> 00:05:45,262
[ sips ]

113
00:05:45,345 --> 00:05:47,306
[ sighs ]

114
00:05:55,147 --> 00:05:58,108
FINN: Come on, dude.
It's time for your vitamins.

115
00:06:07,493 --> 00:06:09,495
[ grumbles ]

116
00:06:12,706 --> 00:06:15,542
Okay. So let's
retrace your steps.

117
00:06:15,626 --> 00:06:18,420
Do you remember which path
you took?

118
00:06:18,504 --> 00:06:19,463
[ cat meows ]

119
00:06:19,546 --> 00:06:21,215
Prince?

120
00:06:25,594 --> 00:06:27,304
Whoa!
You found it already!

121
00:06:27,387 --> 00:06:29,348
Good work, team!

122
00:06:35,103 --> 00:06:37,523
Ow! Quit that!

123
00:06:39,650 --> 00:06:42,236
Come on.
You're a prince.

124
00:06:44,530 --> 00:06:46,406
Come, your majesty.

125
00:06:46,490 --> 00:06:49,034
It's time.

126
00:06:51,703 --> 00:06:53,747
[ cat meows ]

127
00:06:59,795 --> 00:07:02,089
People of the Box Kingdom!

128
00:07:05,092 --> 00:07:06,969
| have found...

129
00:07:07,052 --> 00:07:09,012
your true prince!

130
00:07:13,976 --> 00:07:16,144
J'accuse!

131
00:07:16,228 --> 00:07:22,568
[ cats meow ]

132
00:07:22,651 --> 00:07:24,403
what?

133
00:07:24,486 --> 00:07:26,613
They -- they don't believe us.

134
00:07:26,697 --> 00:07:28,031
Mm.

135
00:07:28,115 --> 00:07:30,534
The rain lumped up your
complexion all hobo-like.

136
00:07:30,617 --> 00:07:34,037
They're not looking past
the surface grunk.

137
00:07:34,121 --> 00:07:37,040
[ cat meows ]

138
00:07:37,124 --> 00:07:39,084
Hmm?

139
00:07:42,129 --> 00:07:44,047
[ cat meows ]

140
00:07:44,131 --> 00:07:46,258
Oh, no. He's challenging you
to a joust!

141
00:07:46,341 --> 00:07:48,594
We better find you a lance.

142
00:07:52,556 --> 00:07:54,474
[ spits ]

143
00:07:54,558 --> 00:07:56,268
Did it come out?

144
00:07:56,351 --> 00:07:58,312
You've forgotten
the most important part,

145
00:07:58,395 --> 00:08:00,022
my impatient little friend --

146
00:08:00,105 --> 00:08:02,065
a thorough rinsing.

147
00:08:07,529 --> 00:08:08,989
Well?

148
00:08:09,072 --> 00:08:10,991
[ spits ]

149
00:08:11,074 --> 00:08:13,201
Bleh.
Nothing.

150
00:08:13,285 --> 00:08:15,537
| need, like, a toothpick
or something.

151
00:08:15,621 --> 00:08:17,581
| told you to buy floss.

152
00:08:17,664 --> 00:08:19,625
Floss is for losers.

153
00:08:25,589 --> 00:08:27,174
Oh, one of these
will do nicely.

154
00:08:27,257 --> 00:08:29,134
You put cards in your mouth?

155
00:08:29,217 --> 00:08:30,552
Just the edge, kid.

156
00:08:30,636 --> 00:08:34,514
And then | work it
like a pro.

157
00:08:34,598 --> 00:08:36,350
Now to find the card
that best suits

158
00:08:36,433 --> 00:08:39,436
my devil-may-care
personality.

159
00:08:40,729 --> 00:08:43,482
[ trumpets blaring ]

160
00:08:43,565 --> 00:08:45,525
[ cats meowing ]

161
00:08:45,609 --> 00:08:46,985
[ cat meows ]

162
00:08:47,069 --> 00:08:49,529
Trial by combat shall
prove which prince is true!

163
00:08:49,613 --> 00:08:51,823
[ both meow ]

164
00:08:51,907 --> 00:08:54,076
[ cat meows ]

165
00:09:05,170 --> 00:09:06,380
[ both meow ]

166
00:09:06,463 --> 00:09:08,173
[ gasps ]

167
00:09:08,256 --> 00:09:10,217
[ both yowling ]

168
00:09:13,637 --> 00:09:15,597
[ cats yowl ]

169
00:09:19,601 --> 00:09:22,229
This town's gone nuts!

170
00:09:23,230 --> 00:09:26,900
[ humming ]

171
00:09:26,984 --> 00:09:29,319
JAKE:
Hey, Beemo!

172
00:09:29,403 --> 00:09:31,154
Ta-da!

173
00:09:31,238 --> 00:09:32,864
[ gasps ]
You did it, Jake!

174
00:09:32,948 --> 00:09:34,199
Congratulations!

175
00:09:34,282 --> 00:09:37,536
How did you get that piece of
tortilla chip out of your teeth?

176
00:09:37,619 --> 00:09:39,538
Oh, | didn't.
It's still there.

177
00:09:39,621 --> 00:09:41,206
It'll be like a constant
reminder

178
00:09:41,289 --> 00:09:43,083
of what life's all
about.

179
00:09:43,166 --> 00:09:46,044
This is unsatisfying.

180
00:09:46,128 --> 00:09:48,046
Zip it!

181
00:09:48,130 --> 00:09:50,465
[ cats yowling ]

182
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:54,469
Hyah!

183
00:09:59,891 --> 00:10:00,726
Bad!

184
00:10:00,809 --> 00:10:02,894
Bad princes!

185
00:10:02,978 --> 00:10:04,938
[ cats meow ]

186
00:10:13,822 --> 00:10:15,782
Which is which?

187
00:10:20,829 --> 00:10:24,207
Aww!

188
00:10:24,291 --> 00:10:27,419
This is the one!
This is your prince!

189
00:10:32,758 --> 00:10:34,217
Um...

190
00:10:34,301 --> 00:10:37,554
or maybe this is the one!

191
00:10:37,637 --> 00:10:41,808
[ cats meow ]

192
00:10:41,892 --> 00:10:44,644
Hmm.

193
00:10:44,728 --> 00:10:48,231
[ cat meows ]

194
00:10:48,315 --> 00:10:50,108
Is this...

195
00:10:50,192 --> 00:10:51,777
is this even a kingdom?

196
00:10:51,860 --> 00:10:53,862
[ cat purring ]

197
00:10:53,945 --> 00:10:56,073
[ cats meowing ]

198
00:10:56,156 --> 00:10:57,407
[ chuckles ]

199
00:10:57,491 --> 00:11:00,619
Aww!
[ chuckles ]

200
00:11:00,702 --> 00:11:02,204
Aww. Hey, hey!

201
00:11:02,287 --> 00:11:03,830
Oh, you guys!

202
00:11:03,914 --> 00:11:04,873
Aww, cut it out!

203
00:11:04,956 --> 00:11:06,374
[ meowing, purring continues ]

204
00:11:06,458 --> 00:11:07,501
Aww! Oh!

205
00:11:07,584 --> 00:11:09,544
Ah!

206
00:11:09,628 --> 00:11:12,214
[ chuckles ]

207
00:11:13,673 --> 00:11:17,719
» Come along with me »

208
00:11:17,803 --> 00:11:21,556
2 And the butterflies and bees

209
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:25,143
» We can wander through the forest J»

210
00:11:25,227 --> 00:11:29,648
2 And do so as we please »

211
00:11:29,731 --> 00:11:33,401
» Come along with me »

212
00:11:33,485 --> 00:11:36,363
D To a cliff under a tree »

213
00:11:40,242 --> 00:11:42,244
FINN:
This party is so crazy!

